Then there's Sister Tisara.

47
00:03:47,235 --> 00:03:52,566
She's also living at Amrawati and is a nun of the same order.

48
00:03:53,748 --> 00:04:01,144
And we have a little connection there because she began her Buddhist practice at Gaia House, where I was the resident teacher at the time.

49
00:04:02,187 --> 00:04:10,376
Then there's Sister Punyanandi, who has ordained in the Burmese tradition of temporary ordination.

50
